menu "Captive Portal"

    config PORTAL_AP_SSID_PREFIX
        string "SoftAP SSID prefix"
        default "NETGEAR-"
        help
            Prefix for the provisioning AP SSID. The last 6 characters are
            derived from a hash of the chip MAC so each device gets a unique
            name that looks like a real router.

            Keep this generic and plausible — use a common consumer router
            brand (e.g. "TP-LINK-", "DLINK-", "HUAWEI-").

            Max 26 characters so the full SSID stays within the 32-char limit.

    comment "The portal AP is always WPA2-protected by an eFuse-derived password"

    config PORTAL_AP_CHANNEL
        int "SoftAP WiFi channel"
        default 6
        range 1 13
        help
            WiFi channel for the provisioning AP. Channel 1, 6, or 11 are
            the standard non-overlapping 2.4 GHz channels.

    config PORTAL_AP_MAX_CONN
        int "Maximum simultaneous portal connections"
        default 1
        range 1 4
        help
            Number of devices that can connect to the portal AP at the same
            time. 1 is recommended — there is no reason for multiple devices
            to configure the relay simultaneously.

    config PORTAL_TIMEOUT_SEC
        int "Portal auto-close timeout in seconds (0 = never)"
        default 300
        range 0 3600
        help
            Seconds after boot before the portal automatically closes and the
            device reboots. If no credentials were entered, the device will
            just reboot back into portal mode again.

            0 disables the timeout — the portal stays open indefinitely.
            Useful for development; not recommended for deployment.

    config PORTAL_HTTP_PORT
        int "Portal HTTP server port"
        default 80
        range 1 65535
        help
            TCP port the portal HTTP server listens on. 80 is required for
            captive portal detection to work correctly on iOS and Android.

endmenu
